What 'verilator' command line do we use to run your example?
```
verilator \ 
--trace --trace-vcd \ 
--unroll-count 4   \
--binary             \
--timing  -j 8        \
--Mdir /var/tmp/verilator_work_dirs/disable_fork/rtl/work  \
--report-unoptflat  \
--bbox-unsup --bbox-sys  \ 
--output-split 200000 \ 
--timescale 1ns/100ps --x-assign unique --x-initial unique \  
  -O3  \
-I/home/verilator_test_cases/ver/th \ 
/home/verilator_test_cases/rtl/disable_fork.sv \
/home/verilator_test_cases/ver/th/disable_fork_tb.sv \
--top-module disable_fork_tb 

```
What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?  Did you try it with other simulators? I am using Verilator 5.04 but I have seen the same issue with the git master

What OS and distribution are you using? Ubuntu 24.04

May we assist you in trying to fix this in Verilator yourself? Unfortunately no

